ell distributed and the fonts work correctly. It is a Latin passage extract=
ed from a text by Cicero, <em>De finibus bonorum et malorum</em>. </p>

<p>However, you don't need to stick to it in your projects. New fake text g=
enerators are constantly popping up and can help you give your designs a tw=
ist, even for provisional text boxes that are not meant to be read. If you =
are one of those who wants to have fun with <em>Lorem ipsum</em>, here are =
some ideas:</p>

